parameters:
\n<Count Noblesse>Well, I presume you all are already aware of this...? No, if
there's anyone who isn't, they may leave right now...? Allow
me to explain once more.
\n<Count Noblesse>Captain~!!!
\n<Captain>Sir!

\n<Captain>The other day, we received a warning letter from that
detestable, vulgar thief \C[14]Phantom "L"\C[0].

\n<Captain>I believe our private soldiers have faced him several times
before, but since we also have personnel from the
Adventurers' Guild this time, let me explain about Phantom
"L" once again.

\n<Captain>"L" is so confident and arrogant that he sends a warning
letter before committing his thefts. He steals people's
wealth and then mocks them. He's nothing but a lump of
exhibitionism and a despicable villain.

\n<Captain>Count Noblesse's mansion alone has already suffered 15
incidents, and the entire noble district has experienced
well over 30 thefts.
\n<Adventurer A>Isn't this place being robbed too much...?
\n<Adventurer B>Could it be that the private soldiers are incompetent?
\n<Captain>Who just spoke out of turn?

\n<Captain>It's a shameful admission, but it's true. We've been
outwitted by "L" time and again, and had our valuables
stolen.

\n<Captain>But this time it's different! In addition to a major
renovation with a moat, we've added barriers, traps, and
more personnel! We've further strengthened our security
beyond what it was before to ensure we're completely
prepared.

\n<Captain>If by some chance we are robbed again, you may as well bury
me under a spruce tree. That's how prepared I am for this
challenge.

\n<Captain>Now, regarding the assignments, our private soldiers will
handle the security inside the mansion, while those
dispatched from the Guild will take care of the outdoor
watch.

\n<Count Noblesse>And if the warning holds true~? The crescent moon. In other
words! The crime will be committed tonight~.

\n<Count Noblesse>Whoever captures the cat will receive an additional~? Ah,
additionally! A special reward of a purse full of gold!
\n<Count Noblesse>Be encouraged~!! And strive on~!!

\n<\n[1]>(This sounds exciting! I'm getting pumped♥ I'll catch them
and get a whole lot of money! Hehehe♥)

\n<\n[1]>(A phantom thief, huh... I don't know what kind of person
they are, but stealing from others is wrong. Alright. I'll
catch them!)
\n<Count Noblesse>...
\n<Count Noblesse>...Captain. I'm counting on you.
\n<Captain>Yes, sir!

\n<Captain>As the captain who was buried under the spruce tree the
other day has been replaced, I have been appointed as the
new captain. I will now read the advance notice from the
phantom thief "L".

\C[14]\n<Captain>Not only the moon shines yellow. Not only wolves howl at the
moon. On a night of a round mirror. Just as your face
reflects on the water's surface. Phantom thief "L"

\n<Captain>From this advance notice, it is presumed that they are
targeting one of the world's four great diamonds, the
\C[14]"Call of the Wolf Stone"\C[0].

\C[14]\n<Captain>The "Call of the Wolf Stone" was so named because it emits a
beautiful yellow light that wolves mistake for the moon and
howl at.

\n<Captain>Normally, even the fact that Count Noblesse possesses it
should be kept a secret.

\n<Captain>This time, we deliberately leaked information about the Call
of the Wolf Stone as bait to lure out phantom thief "L". And
he took the bait splendidly.

\n<Adventurer A>The world's four great diamonds... I've seen them in an
encyclopedia before. I can't believe they really exist...
\n<Adventurer B>If it gets stolen, heads will roll...
\n<Captain>Indeed. But that just shows how serious this is.

\n<Captain>The night of the round mirror refers to a full moon, but it
will take a few more days for the moon to be full. However,
given what's at stake, we will start guarding from tonight.

\n<Captain>Regarding the positions, known private soldiers will be
inside the mansion, and guild reinforcements will take care
of the outside. Also, the former sergeant will be outside as
well.
\n<Former Sergeant>Yes... I'll do my best...

\n<Count Noblesse>This is a kind of gamble. It could be called a clash of
wills. If the Call of the Wolf Stone is stolen, I won't get
off lightly either.

\n<Count Noblesse>But... I will definitely throw Cats into jail and make them
receive their due punishment. Let's make this the last time.
\n<Count Noblesse>...

\n<\n[1]>(Uncle Count seems different from last time? I have a
strange feeling...)

\n<\n[1]>(The Count has a stern look on his face. If only I had
caught him last time... last time...)
\n<\n[1]>(Ugh... let's not dwell on those memories...)
